  <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><div>Use the form below to report new use, re-use - any use, anywhere - of your recorded work. The union often learns of unpaid use of union recordings through our members. Below you will find the definitions of new use and re-use.</div>
<div> </div>
<div>New use: When music recorded in one medium shows up somewhere else -- in a different medium for a different purpose -- then your name on the union contract can mean an additional wage payment. For example, a CD recording used in a film soundtrack is a new use.</div>
<div> </div>
<div>Re-Use: Many electronic media agreements call for additional payments to be made for the continued use of your recorded music. Examples include TV programs and commercial jingles.</div>
<div> </div>
<div>*Denotes Required Field</div>
<div> </div>
</div></div></div>
  
